&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO MATERNITY COVER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an experienced, enthusiastic Community Nurse to join our team on a temporary basis to cover Maternity Leave working within the Central Wrexham District Nursing Service based at Grove Road Health Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Purpose:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post–holder will be responsible for assessing, planning, implementing and evaluating nursing care in the community. He/she will be expected to work collaboratively with the District Nursing Team and other agencies to provide clinically effective care without direct supervision. To support and assist the District Nursing Sister in overall team management and be responsible for deputising in the District Nursing Sister’s absence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 18/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Pierce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sarah.pierce2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;03000 859672&lt;/p&gt;
